# Paths markdownlint must not read.
#
# Only authored Markdown is linted. Per CLAUDE.md, authored Markdown under
# docs/ is canonical and generated output is never the source of truth.

# MkDocs build artefacts.
site/
output/

# Workflow definitions and issue templates are not specification prose.
.github/

# Third-party dependencies.
node_modules/

# templates/ is intentionally NOT excluded.
#
# Template files contain placeholder prose and instructional HTML comments
# describing what an author should write, but they are still authored
# Markdown and must obey the same structural rules — a template that emits a
# malformed list or an unlabelled fence propagates that defect into every
# specification created from it.
#
# The placeholders are prose-level, not structure-level, so the rules enabled
# in .markdownlint.yaml do not conflict with them. Prose-level tooling
# (Vale, lychee) does exempt templates/; see .vale.ini and lychee.toml.
